<P>REader, if thou call in question, what I have said in the Preface, anent the Number of these absurd Te|nets, maintained by the <HI>Cartesian Philosophers</HI> abroad. I refer thee, for full satisfaction, to <HI>Petrus van Mastrick,</HI> that famous <HI>Professor</HI> of <HI>Theology</HI> at <HI>Utricht,</HI> who in his late Book entituled <HI>Gangraena Carte sianismi,</HI> has set them all down, and far more than I have mentioned, cit|ing Author, Book, and Page, and has notably confuted them. For proof of what I have written anent these o|ther Tenets, mentioned in the last Page of the Book, see <HI>Malebranche</HI> his Books, <HI>La Recherche de la Verite. De la Nature, &amp; de la Grace,</HI> and his <HI>Meditations Chrestiens,</HI> together with <HI>Mr. Arnaulds</HI> Book <HI>de Vraes, &amp; de Fausses Idees,</HI> where all these opinions are ridiculed, and most rationally confuted.</P>
